					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 14th or 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<extent rend="visible">272 folios<dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>230</height>
										<width>165</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>160</height>
										<width>115</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>272 folios (+ 2 older and 1 modern unfoliated flyleaves at the beginning, 1 older foliated flyleaf at the beginning, and 2 older and 2 modern unfoliated flyleaves at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>28 quires of mostly 10 leaves each.</p>
									<p>Most of the quires marked with catchwords at the end.</p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 " ruledLines="24" writtenLines="24">
									<p>Pricking and hard-point ruling are visible. </p>
									<p>The books of the Torah, which are commented upon, are separated with two blank lines.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Italian semi-cursive script, not punctuated, of the 14th to 15th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Yitsḥaḳ Merly</name>: inscribed with his name as an author of corrections in the text, folio 2r, in a following subscription: מתוקן על ידי יצחק מארלי. See similar subscription in Harley 5708, <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">171</ref>.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Shelomoh ben Mosheh</name> and <name type="person" role="owner">Shemu᾿el Tsarfati</name>: inscribed in a note of sale, folio 272v.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Yitsḥaḳ (?) ben Yeḳuti᾿el Finzi</name> (?): inscribed, folio 273r.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Giovanni Domenico Carretto</name>: Italian censor (active in the first quarter of the 17th century): inscribed with his name, <date calendar="Gregorian">1618 </date>(folio 271v); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">100-101</ref>. </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Domenico Irosolimitano</name>, Italian censor (active in the last quarter of the 16th and first quarter of the 17th century): inscribed with his name (folio 271v); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">61</ref>. </p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>Post-1600. Black leather with the Harley coat of arms in the centre.</p>
								<p>Spine: 'Rashi on the Pentateuch. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Harl. Or. 5655.'</p>
							</binding>
